description:
Neutrally Bouyant Cable

Description:
Neutrally bouyant cable with 1 x 75 ohm coax, 1 x 1.5 mm2 pair, and 2 x 0.25 mm2 screened twisted pairs, with a Kevlar braid to 160 kg breaking strain, foamed polyolefine inner sheath and polyurethane outer sheath

Construction:
• Coax 75 ohm:1 x 0.14 mm2 tinned copper conductor, foamed polypropylene insulation, tinned copper wire braid, low density polyethylene (LDPE) sheath
• 2 x 1.5 mm2: 2 x 1.5 mm2 stranded aluminium alloy conductors, high density polyethylene (HDPE) insulation
• 2 x (2 x 0.25 mm2): 2 pairs of 0.25 mm2 stranded tinned copper conductors, HDPE insulation, aluminium/polyester tape with tinned copper drain wire
• Conductors laid up with a filler and protective polyester tape overall
• Kevlar braid, breaking strain 160 kg
• Polyurethane outer sheath
• Nominal overall diameter 11.70 mm
